    "text": "Deactivation of Assets Worth Over Rs. 30 Million Acquired by a Drug Trafficker Using Illegally Earned Funds \u2013 Illicit Assets Investigation Division An inquiry has been launched and is currently underway following a complaint received by the Illicit Assets Investigation Division regarding a drug trafficker residing in Colombo 14 who is alleged to have accumulated property and assets through drug-related activities. The Negombo and Colombo High Courts have extended and enforced orders to freeze assets belonging to the suspect, including land in Colombo 14 and Ja-Ela valued at over Rs. 5.14 billion, four commercial outlets, a three-storey residence, and six bank accounts amounting to approximately Rs. 5.9 billion, all believed to have been acquired through illicit earnings. Further investigations have uncovered that proceeds from drug trafficking were used to purchase a luxury three-storey house valued at Rs. 30 million, situated on land in the Wellampitiya area of Wennappuwa, Wennawatta. Orders have been issued to suspend the use of this property for a period of seven days, effective from 20.03.2026. Additional inquiries are being carried out by the Illicit Assets Investigation Division. Police Media Division",
    "fonts": [
      "IskoolaPota-Bold",
      "TimesNewRomanPS-BoldMT",
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  }
